## Dimension: Traceability

**Definition**: The degree to which every statement can be traced to specific sources via explicit citations, enabling verification and audit.

**Why This Matters**: Transparent scientific advice requires complete audit trails. Experts reviewing Delphi feedback must be able to verify claims against source material. Missing citations undermine trust and auditability.

